Day 5 - Chapter 2
2) For loops in the range() function
=> for with range() is used when you want to repeat something a specific number of times or step through a sequence of numbers.

Common forms of range();- 
i. range(stop) → 0 to stop - 1
for i in range(3):   # 0, 1, 2
    print(i)
ii. range(start, stop) → start to stop - 1
for i in range(1, 4):  # 1, 2, 3
    print(i)
iii. range(start, stop, step) → with a step
for i in range(0, 10, 2):  # 0, 2, 4, 6, 8
    print(i)

